value.value: 胸腺髄質の矮小化
decreased size of the inner area of thymus lobules
胸腺髄質の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the thymus medulla, typically resulting in decreased size
胸腺髄質の肥大化
increased size of the inner area of thymus lobules
胸腺髄質の過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the thymus medulla, typically resulting in increased size
胸腺皮質の矮小化
decreased size of the outer part of a thymus lobule that surrounds the medulla and is composed of closely packed lymphocytes
胸腺皮質の肥大化
increased size of the outer part of a thymus lobule that surrounds the medulla and is composed of closely packed lymphocytes
耳下腺房の形態異常

any structural anomaly of any of the secretory units (acini) of either parotid gland which in human and rodent consist almost exclusively of serous secretory cells with their lumina continuous with intercalated ducts; in mouse, parotid gland acini are very small and consist of 3-4 tall pyramidal cells with strongly basophilic cytoplasm and basally located, large spherical nuclei; the serous secretory cells contain many secretory granules having an electron-lucent profile which are situated in the supranuclear cytoplasm; the serous secretory cells have a well-developed rough endoplasmic reticulum in the infranuclear region and are surrounded by myoepithelial cells
鋤鼻器官の欠如

lacking the tubular, crescent-sensory organ with a luminal epithelium that contains chemosensitive receptor cells with microvilli that are thought to detect pheromones and transmit signals to the remainder of the accessory olfactory system

definition.value: Note that this structure is normally absent in adult higher primates as well as a number of other species.

value.value: 鋤鼻器官の生理異常

any functional anomaly of the tubular, crescent-sensory organ with a luminal epithelium that contains chemosensitive receptor cells with microvilli that are thought to detect pheromones and transmit signals to the remainder of the accessory olfactory system; the organ lies at the base the nasal cavity and is split into two, separated by the nasal septum
鋤鼻器官の矮小化

reduced size of the tubular, crescent-sensory organ with a luminal epithelium that contains chemosensitive receptor cells with microvilli that are thought to detect pheromones and transmit signals to the remainder of the accessory olfactory system
ライディッヒ細胞の肥大
increased size of the interstitial cells that are found adjacent to the seminiferous tubules in the testicle and produce testosterone in the presence of luteinizing hormone (LH)
ライディッヒ細胞の萎縮

acquired diminution of the interstitial cells that are found adjacent to the seminiferous tubules in the testicle and produce testosterone in the presence of luteinizing hormone (LH), associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
精巣の変性
a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of either or both of the male reproductive glands
精巣のアポトーシス増加
increase in the number of cells in testicular tissue undergoing programmed cell death
ライディッヒ細胞の分化異常

atypical formation of or inability to produce the interstitial cells that are found adjacent to the seminiferous tubules in the testicle and produce testosterone in the presence of luteinizing hormone; in most mammals, normal Leydig cell (LC) development comprises two sequential but overlapping cell lineages known as the fetal and adult type LC populations, which display distinct functional characteristics reflected by different morphology, hormonal regulation, and steroidogenic output
胎児のライディッヒ細胞の分化異常

atypical formation of or inability to produce the first or fetal population of Leydig cells (FLCs); in mice, FLCs arise in the testicular interstitium between E12.5 and E13.0, approximately 1 day after the appearance of Sertoli cells; Sertoli cells trigger differentiation of steroidogenic factor 1-positive (SF1-positive) progenitor cells into FLCs via paracrine regulation; the intercellular Notch signaling pathway is also involved in FLC establishment and maintenance; the FLC population increases dramatically during embryonic development despite the fact that differentiating FLCs are mitotically inactive, suggesting that expansion of FLC populations results from differentiation of progenitor cells, rather than cell division of existing FLCs; the SF1-positive cells in gonadal primordia are the primary source of FLCs but other sources such as neighboring mesonephros, migrating neural crest cells, and cells from the coelomic epithelium or interstitium are potential contributors also; at the end of fetal life and during the first 2 postnatal weeks in rodents, FLCs are gradually replaced by adult Leydig cells (ALCs)
成体のライディッヒ細胞分化異常

atypical formation of or inability to produce the second or adult population of Leydig cells (ALCs) between birth and puberty; ALCs arise in the interstitium of adult testes from unknown progenitor cells and become the major source of androgens that control differentiation of the male reproductive tract and spermatogenesis; ALCs are not derived from fetal Leydig cells (FLCs), and the origin and the molecular events that control ALC differentiation are poorly understood
卵巣嚢の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the peritoneal recess between the medial aspect of the ovary and the mesosalpinx
卵巣窩の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the shallow depression in the parietal peritoneum of the pelvis that lodges the ovary
卵巣の線維化
invasion of fibrous connective tissue into the ovary, often resulting from inflammation or injury
卵巣皮質の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the layer of the ovarian stroma lying immediately beneath the tunica albuginea, composed of connective tissue cells and fibers, among which are scattered primary and secondary (antral) follicles in various stages of development; the cortex varies in thickness according to the age of the individual, becoming thinner with advancing years; included in the follicles are the cumulus oophorus, membrana granulosa (and the granulosa cells inside it), corona radiata, zona pellucida, and primary oocyte; the zona pellucida, theca of follicle, antrum and liquor folliculi are also contained in the follicle; also in the cortex is the corpus luteum derived from the follicles
卵巣髄質の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the highly vascular stroma found in the center of the ovary that forms from embryonic mesenchyme and contains blood vessels, lymphatic vessels, and nerves; this stroma forms the tissue of the hilum by which the ovarian ligament is attached, and through which the blood vessels enter
卵巣網の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the canal structure formed from the primary sex cords in females; a transient network of cells in the developing ovary that is homologous to the rete testis in males
胆管上皮形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelium lining the intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile ducts
尾側椎骨の肥大化
increased size of the bony segments of the coccyx or tail

definition.value: There are usually 27-30 caudal vertebrae present in rodents and only 3-5 fused caudal vertebrae in human.

value.value: 体積骨密度の異常

anomaly of the mineral mass per unit volume of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; this is expressed as the amount of mineral per cubic cm of bone (usually in mgHA/cm^3), with results generated from Quantitative computed tomography (QCT) and other tests
骨密度面積異常

anomaly of the mineral mass per unit area of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; expressed as the amount of mineral per area cm^2 of bone (usually in g/cm^2), with results generated from Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA or DEXA) tests
体積骨密度の増加

increase in the mineral mass per unit volume of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; this is expressed as the amount of mineral per cubic cm of bone (usually in mgHA/cm^3), with results generated from Quantitative computed tomography (QCT) and other tests
体積骨密度の減少

reduction in the mineral mass per unit volume of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; this is expressed as the amount of mineral per cubic cm of bone (usually in mgHA/cm^3), with results generated from Quantitative computed tomography (QCT) and other tests
面積骨密度の増加

increase in the mineral mass per unit area of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; expressed as the amount of mineral per area cm^2 of bone (usually in g/cm^2), with results generated from Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA or DEXA) tests
面積骨密度の減少

reduction of the mineral mass per unit area of bone, the hard, rigid form of connective tissue constituting most of the skeleton of vertebrates and composed chiefly of calcium salts; expressed as the amount of mineral per area cm^2 of bone (usually in g/cm^2), with results generated from Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA or DEXA) tests
長骨内径の異常

anomaly of the cross-sectional distance that extends from one lateral edge of a long bone marrow cavity, through its center and to the opposite lateral edge of the bone marrow cavity through the mid point of the bone
大腿骨内径の増加

increased cross-sectional distance that extends from one lateral edge of the femur long bone marrow cavity, through its center and to the opposite lateral edge of the bone marrow cavity through the mid point of the femur
大腿骨内径の減少

reduced cross-sectional distance that extends from one lateral edge of the femur long bone marrow cavity, through its center and to the opposite lateral edge of the bone marrow cavity through the mid point of the femur
大腿骨緻密骨の厚さ異常
reduced or increased width of the superficial layer of compact bone at the midpoint of the femur
大腿骨緻密骨の厚さ増加
increased width of the superficial layer of compact bone at the midpoint of the femur
大腿骨緻密骨の厚さ減少
reduced width of the superficial layer of compact bone at the midpoint of the femur
大腿骨の降伏荷重増加
increase in load (N) on the femur at which elastic deformation ends
大腿骨の降伏荷重減少
decrease in load (N) on the femur at which elastic deformation ends
椎骨の降伏荷重増加
increase in load (N) on a vertebra at which elastic deformation ends
椎骨の降伏荷重減少
decrease in load (N) on a vertebra at which elastic deformation ends
骨梁間隔異常
any deviation in the amount of space between trabeculae in cancellous bone
海綿骨の骨梁中心距離延長
increase in the amount of space between trabeculae in cancellous bone
骨梁の間隔が減少
decrease in the amount of space between trabeculae in cancellous bone
大腿骨の最大荷重増加
increase in the maximal load (N) that can be sustained by the femur
大腿骨の最大荷重減少
decrease in the maximal load (N) that can be sustained by the femur
大腿骨の骨折荷重増加
increase in the load at which material failure occurs after plastic deformation
大腿骨の骨折荷重減少
decrease in the load at which material failure occurs after plastic deformation
骨硬度異常
deviation in material stiffness (N/mm) during elastic deformation
大腿骨の骨硬度増加
increase in material stiffness (N/mm) during elastic deformation in the femur
